<TEXT>
<P>
 AmeriQuest To Acquire Valley Software Distributor: As part of the 
consolidation of the personal computer industry, Kenfil Inc. of Van Nuys will 
become a division of AmeriQuest Technologies. The all-stock deal will nearly 
triple the Irvine-based microcomputer parts distributor's annual sales.Some 
layoffs among the 300 employees are likely among warehousing and administrative 
positions. Kenfil, with 150 employees and $191 million in sales last year, is 
one of the nation's largest software distributors. AmeriQuest, formerly called 
CMS Enhancements, has begin an aggressive expansion campaign after shrinking 
from $200 million in sales in 1989 to just $73 million last year. At Tuesday's 
closing price of $4.50 for AmeriQuest common stock, the deal would be worth 
$17.5 million. But the value will depend on the stock prices when shares are 
exchanged in two installments 60 and 105 days from now. 
</P>
