<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: CATALINA; WOMAN KILLED 
AS PLANE CRASHES, SETS OFF BRUSH FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A light plane crashed Tuesday night in a patch of rugged chaparral on Santa 
Catalina Island, killing at least one occupant and igniting a quarter-acre 
brush fire that was visible for miles, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles County Sheriff's Deputy Burt Lyon said the crash was reported at 
7:11 p.m. in the Big Springs area of the island about 3 1/2 miles west of the 
Catalina-Avalon Airport. A woman's body was found in the Cessna's wreckage two 
hours later as paramedics searched for survivors. 
</P>
<P>
 The Big Springs area is in the center of land owned by the Santa Catalina 
Island Conservancy. The cause of the crash was not immediately determined. 
</P>
