<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: BUSINESS CONFERENCE SCHEDULED APRIL 13 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRED ALVAREZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura County Economic Development Assn. will host its 24th annual 
Business Outlook Conference on April 13. 
</P>
<P>
 The conference -- which will feature experts in the areas of economy, health 
and education -- is designed to help business people cope with the 
recession-choked economy. 
</P>
<P>
 Topics of discussion will include "The Clinton Health Plan," "Free Choice 
Alternative to the Clinton Plan" and "From Student Development to Economic 
Development: Quiet Revolution." 
</P>
<P>
 The conference will be held at the Oxnard Hilton Inn, 600 Esplanade Drive. The 
program starts at 7:15 a.m. and runs through 1:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Registration is $60 for VCEDA members and $75 for non-members. Prospective 
participants are encouraged to register in advance, although registration also 
will be allowed at the door on the day of the event. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call VCEDA at 988-1106. FRED ALVAREZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
