<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MASKED GUNMAN ROBS CARD CLUB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police are investigating a robbery at a Ventura card club early Tuesday in 
which a man held a gun to one patron's head while demanding cash from other 
customers. 
</P>
<P>
 The holdup occurred just before 1 a.m. at the Ash Street Card Club, which is 
operated out of the Elks Lodge building at 11 S. Ash St. No one was injured, 
and investigators would not disclose how much cash was taken. 
</P>
<P>
 According to police and witnesses, a man clad in black clothing and a black 
ski mask accosted a 22-year-old man in the building's rear parking lot, placed 
a gun to his head and ordered him to walk inside the club. 
</P>
<P>
 Inside, six patrons playing poker and three employees were forced to get down 
on the ground and then to empty out their pockets. The suspect told several 
patrons to put the cash inside a backpack and ordered a manager to empty the 
cash drawer. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspect then made the man kneel on the floor and hand the backpack over 
his head, and the robber fled. 
</P>
<P>
 Police have no suspects, but believe the holdup was well-planned. 
</P>
<P>
 "This suspect is more than likely familiar with that establishment and knew 
what he was doing," Ventura Police Sgt. Bob Anderson said. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
