EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; PAY RAISE CONSIDERED FOR CITY MANAGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Moorpark City Council will consider giving a raise to City Manager Steve 
Kueny at tonight's City Council meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 If approved, the raise would lift Kueny's annual salary to nearly $93,000. 
</P>
<P>
 The council reviewed Kueny's performance over the past year and determined he 
deserved the merit-based pay increase.  
</P>
<P>
 "It amounts to a roughly 2% raise," Moorpark Mayor Paul Lawrason said. 
</P>
<P>
 "He's done a good job," Lawrason said. 
</P>
<P>
 Councilman Scott Montgomery said the council waited to consider Kueny's boost 
in pay until it was sure there was enough money in the budget. 
</P>
<P>
 "Essentially, (Kueny) was charged with the responsibility of keeping the 
budget low enough to cover his possible raise," Montgomery said. 
</P>
<P>
 Kueny has worked for the city since 1984. SCOTT HADLY 
