EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; DISASTER AID OFFICE OPENS FOR 
BUSINESSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Simi Valley businesses struggling to get back on their feet after the Jan. 17 
earthquake can get help close to home, thanks to a disaster aid program that 
has opened a satellite office in town. 
</P>
<P>
 Fueled by state and federal disaster funds, the Small Business Development 
Center of North Los Angeles has opened an office at the Simi Valley Chamber of 
Commerce. 
</P>
<P>
