<P>
DENTURES DEFLECT GUNSHOT FROM ROBBER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 66-year-old man credits his dentures with deflecting a gunshot and saving 
his life, police said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Richard Daniel was sitting outside his house during the weekend when a young 
man on a bicycle pointed a gun at him and demanded his wallet, police said. 
Daniel pulled a knife from his pocket and began struggling with the robber, who 
shot upward at Daniel's chin. 
</P>
<P>
 The dentures split but stopped the bullet from penetrating farther into 
Daniel's head, police said. He was treated at a hospital and released. 
</P>
<P>
 The gunman got away with Daniel's wallet but suffered stab wounds on his chest 
and hand. 
</P>
