<TEXT>
<P>
 "Paint Your Heart Out Anaheim," which provides free painting and minor 
maintenance to low-income senior citizens and disabled residents, is still 
seeking volunteers for its May 7 event. 
</P>
<P>
 Some 46 homes will be painted that day by teams of 15 to 25 volunteers. 
Materials will be donated by local hardware stores. 
</P>
<P>
 Since its founding in 1990, the program has painted 109 homes. 
</P>
<P>
