<TEXT>
<P>
 GATT Predicts Growth in World Trade: World trade should expand by 2.5% to 5% 
this year, depending on the extent and timing of economic recovery in Japan and 
Western Europe, according to the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade.GATT, 
in a report to be released today, said that in volume terms, global exports 
grew by 2.5% in 1993, slowing their rise after expanding 4.5% a year earlier. 
In value terms, merchandise trade dropped by 2% to $3.58 trillion last year. 
Slack trade growth was due mainly to recession in Western Europe, where exports 
and imports fell for the first time in 40 years. 
</P>
