ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; 4 HOME-INVASION ROBBERS SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police are seeking a group of teen-agers who forced their way into a home in 
the 13000 block of Palomar Street early Tuesday, tied up the owners and fled 
with an undisclosed amount of money and jewelry. 
</P>
<P>
 According to police, the robbery took place between 5:00 and 5:30 a.m. The two 
victims, whose names were not revealed, described their assailants as four 
Asian teens who had pulled their shirts over their faces. 
</P>
<P>
 No one was hurt, said Officer Marcus Frank. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the county's latest home-invasion robbery. Since 1991, more than 150 
such attacks, conducted mainly by Asian and Latino gangs, have been reported in 
Westminster, Garden Grove and Santa Ana, authorities have said. 
