<HEADLINE>
<P>
3 TEEN-AGERS KILLED, 1 HURT IN CAR WRECK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three teen-agers were killed and one was seriously injured in a traffic 
accident late Tuesday night, Orange County fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Few details were available, but authorities said the accident occurred at 
Aliso Creek Road and Laguna Hills Drive just before 10:30 p.m.  
</P>
<P>
 Streets near the isolated, South County accident scene were blocked to traffic 
by the California Highway Patrol. 
</P>
<P>
 Three teen-agers, who were not identified, were reported dead at the scene. 
Another was taken to Mission Hospital Regional Medical Center with serious 
injuries. 
</P>
