<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: HE COMES FOR A TROUT AND LEAVES WITH RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John Masek got a clue when the "tree" began to swim. 
</P>
<P>
 "At first, I thought I had snagged an underwater tree," Masek said. "But after 
a few seconds, the fish began to fight. I had no idea what was on the end of 
the line. Then, when I finally saw it, I couldn't believe it." 
</P>
<P>
 What Masek, of Mission Viejo, had on the end of the line was an Irvine 
Lake-record rainbow trout, which tipped the scale at 18 pounds 2 ounces. The 
fish, caught on a chrome Kastmaster lure, eclipsed the previous record by 3 1/2 
pounds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
