<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL / DAILY REPORT; ACROSS THE NATION; ELLIS TAKES AUBURN JOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When Cliff Ellis resigned after a decade as Clemson's basketball coach, he 
said he was looking for new challenges. He found a big one, taking over an 
Auburn team that has had only one winning season in six years. 
</P>
<P>
 After a three-week search that involved at least two other coaches removing 
themselves from consideration, Ellis agreed to a five-year contract to replace 
Tommy Joe Eagles, whose record in five seasons was 64-78. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Clemson basketball player Devin Gray was in serious condition after an 
apparent heart attack. 
</P>
<P>
 He was in the coronary care unit at Greenville (S.C.) Memorial Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Gray, a starting forward who averaged 14.4 points and six rebounds as a junior 
last season, suffered chest pains Monday night, about 50 minutes after a 
conditioning session at Littlejohn Coliseum, the school said. Earlier in the 
day, he had lifted weights and played several pickup basketball games. 
</P>
