<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; AMTRAK TRAIN CLIPS TRUCK NEAR TRACKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHIP JOHNSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Amtrak passenger train clipped a truck parked too close to the tracks at a 
railroad crossing on Balboa Boulevard in Van Nuys on Tuesday morning, a company 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The truck was hit about 10:40 a.m. by the Coast Starlight, which runs between 
Los Angeles and Seattle, said an unidentified company spokesman in 
Philadelphia. No one was injured, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The train was delayed 22 minutes at the scene, he said. Before the accident, 
it had left Los Angeles' Union Station at 9:55 a.m., with one stop in Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
 "This happens between 15 and 20 times a year all around the nation," he said. 
CHIP JOHNSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
