<HEADLINE>
<P>
AVERAGE BASEBALL SALARY RISES TO $1,188,679; MONEY: YANKEES ARE TOP-PAID CLUB 
AT $1,760,974. DODGERS ARE AT $1,457,552, ANGELS AT $750,268. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The average baseball salary rose 6.1% this year, to $1,188,679 on opening day, 
according to a survey by The Associated Press. 
</P>
<P>
 The New York Yankees are the top-paid team for the first time since 1988. 
</P>
<P>
 New York Met third baseman Bobby Bonilla is the highest-paid player at $6.3 
million, according to an examination of the contract terms for 746 players on 
opening day rosters and disabled lists. 
</P>
<P>
 Chicago Cub second baseman Ryne Sandberg, the salary leader last season, was 
second at $6,299,966. 
</P>
<P>
 The Yankees' average was $1,760,974, up slightly from their $1,759,429 average 
on Aug. 31, 1993, the last day before rosters expanded. Toronto, first last 
year at $1,765,582, dropped to fifth this opening day at $1,498,667. 
</P>
<P>
 The Detroit Tigers, with a major league-leading 15 million-dollar players, 
rose to second at $1,594,700 from 10th at $1,265,317. Atlanta remained third 
but dropped to $1,500,080 from $1,676,211. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dodgers' average salary declined from $1,457,552 on opening day last 
season to $1,426,346 this year, ninth in baseball. It was led by Tom 
Candiotti's $3,650,000, with Brett Butler, Tim Wallach, Orel Hershiser and 
Darryl Strawberry earning more than $3 million. There were 12 Dodger 
millionaires. 
</P>
<P>
 The Angels' average increased from $718,686 last year to $750,268 in 1994, but 
it is still ahead of only the San Diego Padres. Chuck Finley is the 
highest-paid Angel at $3,875,000. There were six Angel millionaires. 
</P>
<P>
 While the number of million-dollar players on opening day rose only slightly, 
to 265 from 262, the total of $2 million players rose to 192 from 182 and $3 
million players increased to 119 from 99. There are 43 $4 million players, an 
increase of six, and 14 $5 million players, an increase of two. 
</P>
<P>
 The 6.1% rise from last year's opening day average of $1,120,254 was less than 
the 8.9% increase in average ticket prices, to $10.45 from $9.60, the 
Chicago-based Team Marketing Report said. 
</P>
<P>
 Yankee Stadium in New York has the highest average ticket price at $14.44, up 
from $13.48 last season.  
</P>
<P>
 Mile High Stadium in Denver has the lowest average at $7.90.  
</P>
<P>
 The cost for a family of four to attend a game -- including two beers, four 
hot dogs, four soft drinks, two caps, two programs and parking -- rose 5.5%, to 
$95.80 from $90.84. The Yankees had the highest cost at $115.25. 
</P>
<P>
 Cincinnati was the low at $79.31. 
</P>
<P>
 The Angels hiked their average ticket price from $8.02 to $8.06, with a family 
average going from $84.60 to $90.24. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dodgers' average ticket price rose from $9.15 to $9.68, with a family 
average going from $88.60 to $90.73. ANGEL SALARIES Chuck Finley: $3,875,000 
Mark Langston: 3,550,000 Chili Davis: 2,400,000 *Joe Magrane: 1,500,000 Spike 
Owen: 1,250,000 Bo Jackson: 1,000,000 Joe Grahe: 925,000 Greg Myers: 700,000 
Dwight Smith: 700,000 Chad Curtis: 600,000 Tim Salmon: 600,000 Gary DiSarcina: 
400,000 John Dopson: 400,000 Craig Lefferts: 400,000 Bob Patterson: 400,000 
Mark Leiter: 300,000 Rex Hudler: 275,000 Harold Reynolds: 230,000 Bill Sampen: 
225,000 *Julio Valera: 175,000 Damion Easley: 170,000 Scott Lewis: 155,000 Mike 
Butcher: 150,000 Phillip Leftwich: 140,000 Eduardo Perez: 135,000 Christopher 
Turner: 125,000 Jim Edmonds: 117,500 *Paul Swingle: 110,000 DODGER SALARIES Tom 
Candiotti: $3,650,000 Brett Butler: 3,500,000 Tim Wallach: 3,412,500 Orel 
Hershiser: 3,333,333 Darryl Strawberry: 3,300,000 Delino Deshields: 2,700,000 
Kevin Gross: 2,700,000 Ramon Martinez: 2,687,500 Todd Worrell: 2,416,667 Jim 
Gott: 1,800,000 *Cory Snyder: 1,500,000 Roger McDowell: 1,350,000 Eric Karros: 
650,000 Mike Piazza: 600,000 Mitch Webster: 600,000 Jose Offerman: 515,000 Jeff 
Treadway: 500,000 Gary Wayne: 350,000 Pedro Astacio: 325,000 Dave Hansen: 
275,000 Carlos Hernandez: 265,000 Henry Rodriguez: 177,000 Rafael Bournigal: 
134,000 Raul Mondesi: 126,000 Darren Dreifort: 109,000 Chan Ho Park: 109,000 
</P>
<P>
 * on disabled list. 
</P>
