<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL ROUNDUP; MATER DEI ERRORS PAVE THE WAY FOR ETHERTON, DANA HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON H. REID 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Standout pitcher Seth Etherton needs few breaks to win baseball games, 
especially when the Dana Hills High senior right-hander is on his game. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei, however, did its best to accommodate Etherton in the Dolphins' 4-1 
South Coast League victory Tuesday at Mater Dei. 
</P>
<P>
 The Monarchs (9-5-1, 4-1 in league play) had as many hits as errors (three) in 
falling into a three-way tie for first with Dana Hills (9-6-1, 4-1) and San 
Clemente.  
</P>
<P>
 Relying on his changeup more than usual, Etherton (5-0) pitched a complete 
game, striking out nine. He retired 15 in a row after giving up a single and a 
walk to the first two batters in the bottom of the first inning. 
</P>
<P>
 "They were really laying off the high fastball, so I said to myself, 'I got to 
get the off-speed stuff over,' " Etherton said. "I felt I got them off-balance 
with the change." 
</P>
<P>
 Talented Monarch sophomore right-hander Mike Hessman (4-1) gave up two 
unearned runs in six innings. Hessman was replaced by senior right-hander Adam 
Harris, who also gave up two unearned runs. 
</P>
<P>
 "You just can't give up free runs," Mater Dei Coach Bob Ickes said. "You just 
can't give up those things with a guy like (Etherton)." JASON H. REID 
</P>
</TEXT>
