<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; BOLLE LEADS EL MODENA'S EASY VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kristi Bolle hit a grand slam and a two-run home run, drove in seven runs and 
scored four to lead El Modena to a 14-0 victory over host Costa Mesa in a 
nonleague softball game called after six innings because of the mercy rule. 
</P>
<P>
 Bolle drove in one of her runs with her third hit of the game, a single, and 
Jennie Foyle also had three hits, scored three runs and had two runs batted in 
for the Vanguards, who scored five runs in the third inning and added two in 
the fourth, four in the fifth and three runs in the sixth. In other nonleague 
softball: 
</P>
<P>
