<HEADLINE>
<P>
THREE TITAN GYMNASTS ON BIG WEST ACADEMIC TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cal State Fullerton gymnastics program placed three athletes on the Big 
West Conference's All-Academic team, which was released Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Christi Clifford, Kristi Mardyn and Karena Mills made the team.Mardyn, a 
sophomore biology major from Coquitlam, Canada, had the highest grade-point 
average of any team member (3.91) and the sixth-highest among all conference 
athletes. 
</P>
<P>
 Clifford, a sophomore kinesiology/health promotion major, had a GPA of 3.53; 
Mills, a senior majoring in biology, had a GPA of 3.53. 
</P>
<P>
 There were 77 conference athletes who maintained at least a 3.2 grade-point 
average, competed in at least 50% of their program's competition and were 
sophomores or higher. This is the first time the Big West Conference has named 
an all-academic team. Other local athletes honored: 
</P>
<P>
 Women's basketball -- Fullerton's Shayla Bradshaw, sophomore, undeclared 
major, 3.37; UC Irvine's Michelle Kahler, junior, social sciences/economics, 
3.45. 
</P>
<P>
 Men's swimming and diving -- UCI's Elijah Fan, sophomore, undeclared, 3.27; 
Pat McDonough, junior, social sciences, 3.79. 
</P>
<P>
 Women's swimming and diving -- UCI's Dena Amr, junior, biological sciences, 
3.53; April Gibbs, junior, biological services, 3.78. 
</P>
</TEXT>
