<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: BOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jim Parque 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Crescenta Valley 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Baseball 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: The senior left-hander has a 5-1 record and an 0.43 
earned-run average. In 40 innings, he has struck out 79. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: In 10 innings last week, Parque had 24 strikeouts and gave 
up seven hits and two earned runs. In a 10-2 victory at Hoover, he pitched a 
six-hitter and struck out 14. On Saturday, Parque pitched only three innings 
because of the state rule that limits pitchers to 10 innings a week. Parque 
struck out 10, four in the third inning after a Montclair Prep batter reached 
base on a passed ball. That resulted in an unearned run and saddled him with 
the loss in a 4-3 defeat. "He continues to impress everybody," Falcon Coach 
Tony Zarrillo said. "He just has a great blend of pitches." 
</P>
</TEXT>
