<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Palmdale 2, Quartz Hill 1 -- Chris Paxton scored on Shad Martin's sacrifice 
fly in the eighth inning of the Golden League showdown at Palmdale (10-3, 3-1). 
Paxton doubled with one out and moved to third on a passed ball. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Hart 6, Canyon 3 -- Aaron Dean hit a three-run home run in the fifth inning, 
giving the visiting Indians (7-3, 3-0) the lead in a Foothill League game. Dean 
also had a triple. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Burroughs 4, Crescenta Valley 3 -- Freshman Anthony Fabrizio drove in Mike 
Bassett with the go-ahead run with two out in the sixth inning of a Babe Herman 
tournament game at Stengel Field. Bassett also pitched a complete game, 
scattering 10 hits for Burroughs (8-6). 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 South Gate 6, Montclair Prep 2 -- The Mounties (8-4) made five errors and 
walked eight in a Babe Herman tournament semifinal. Josh Persell drove in both 
Montclair Prep runs. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Taft 4, Granada Hills 3 -- Scott Horowitz and Greg Venger had run-scoring 
singles in the seventh inning for host Taft (7-6, 2-0) in a Northwest Valley 
Conference game. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 El Camino Real 5, Cleveland 0 -- Randy Wolf (5-1) allowed four hits and struck 
out 14. Steve Riback (two for four) drove in two runs. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Chatsworth 11, San Fernando 5 -- Josh Rawitch was three for four with two 
RBIs, leading the host Chancellors (11-3, 2-0) in a Northwest Valley Conference 
game. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas 6, Santa Paula 1 -- Anthony Kaufman of Calabasas (8-2, 3-2) hit a 
two-run home run and singled home a run to back the three-hit pitching of Josh 
Morton in a Frontier League game at Santa Paula. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Chaminade 3, Modesto Downey 0 -- Joel Orme (3-2) threw a two-hitter for 
Chaminade. In a later game, Chaminade defeated Stockton St. Mary's, 5-1, and 
Orme pitched the first two innings. Orme was four for six in the two games. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Grant 7, Canoga Park 3 -- Aaron Amitin and Rudy Velasquez each had two hits 
and two RBIs and Tony Iovino pitched a three-hitter, leading the host Lancers 
(4-5, 1-2) in a Valley Pac-8 Conference game. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Buena 2, San Marcos 0 -- Jason Kimble's two-run homer in the fifth inning 
lifted Buena (8-3, 4-1) in a Channel League game. Rick Guzman had the only 
other two hits for Buena. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 L.A. Baptist 7, Acalanes 5 -- Nate Laufer was two for two and drove in a run 
for L.A. Baptist (7-4) in the consolation semifinals of the Gladstone 
tournament in Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Oxnard 5, Ventura 4 -- Manuel Canales was three for three with two doubles and 
a home run, leading the visiting Yellowjackets (3-7-1, 1-4-1) in a Channel 
League game. Canales also pitched a complete game, striking out six. HIGH 
SCHOOL SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Saugus 3, Canyon 0 -- Jamie Gillies (11-2) pitched her sixth shutout and Kelli 
Kranz homered and tripled. 
</P>
